      <h2>Safety Instructions</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Always wear proper eye protection while using this handpiece.</strong>
      </div>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Never use a damaged, bent, vibrating, or out-of-balance accessory.</strong>
      </div>

      <div class="note">
        See your Power Tool Owner&rsquo;s Manual for complete instructions on use, care, and maintenance.
      </div>

      <h2>Adjusting the Shaft and Sheath</h2>

      <p>Before attaching this handpiece to your Foredom flex shaft tool, check the sheath and shaft tip and adjust them properly.</p>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h30/p00_04.jpg" alt="Diagram of shaft and sheath showing set screw, motor connector, motor coupling, and motor shaft" />
        <figcaption>Shaft and sheath adjustment &mdash; the tip of the flexible shaft should extend 3/4&Prime; beyond the end of the sheath</figcaption>
      </div>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h30/p00_06.jpg" alt="Close-up of shaft tip extending 3/4 inch beyond sheath" />
        <figcaption>Shaft tip extending 3/4&Prime; beyond the sheath</figcaption>
      </div>

      <ol>
        <li>Hang the motor and shaft/sheath fully extended, or lay them on a flat surface.</li>
        <li>Loosen the set screw in the motor connector.</li>
        <li>Slide the sheath in or out until the tip of the flexible shaft extends 3/4&Prime; beyond the end of the sheath.</li>
        <li>When properly adjusted, tighten the set screw in the motor connector.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Always make sure your power tool is unplugged during any maintenance procedure.</strong>
      </div>

      <h2>Attaching the Handpiece</h2>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h30/p00_03.jpg" alt="Key tip on end of shaft and keyway slot inside back end of handpiece" />
        <figcaption>Key tip connection &mdash; align the key tip of the flexible shaft with the keyway slot in the back end of the handpiece</figcaption>
      </div>

      <ol>
        <li>Look into the back end of the handpiece and locate the keyway slot.</li>
        <li>Align the key tip of the flexible shaft with the keyway slot. If the key is not aligned, turn the shaft tip or the handpiece until they line up.</li>
        <li>Push the handpiece onto the shaft and sheath.</li>
      </ol>

      <p>To remove the handpiece, simply pull it off the shaft and sheath with a firm grip while the motor is not running.</p>

      <div class="note">
        H.30SJ handpieces have a &ldquo;slip joint&rdquo; connection for use with European-style machines. The key tip illustration does not apply to slip joint connections.
      </div>

      <h2>Changing Accessories</h2>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h30/p00_01.jpg" alt="Using chuck key to tighten the 3-jaw chuck on the handpiece" />
        <figcaption>Use the included chuck key to open and close the 3-jaw chuck</figcaption>
      </div>

      <ol>
        <li>Open the chuck jaws as far as necessary using the included chuck key.</li>
        <li>Insert the shank of the accessory fully into the chuck.</li>
        <li>Tighten each of the jaws with the chuck key until the accessory is secure and centered.</li>
        <li>If the accessory does not run true, reopen the jaws, rotate the accessory, and retighten.</li>
        <li>To release an accessory, reopen the chuck jaws with the key and pull it out.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Accessories and Bench-Top Tools</h2>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h30/p00_02.jpg" alt="Foredom H.30 mounted in MAHH-30 handpiece holder with sanding disc" />
        <figcaption>The MAHH-30 handpiece holder clamps to a workbench and holds the H.30 for hands-free operation</figcaption>
      </div>

      <p>A handpiece holder (MAHH-30) is available that clamps to work benches up to 2-1/4&Prime; thick. The height above the bench can be adjusted, and the handpiece can be swiveled and locked into position.</p>

      <p>Bench-top attachments compatible with the H.30 include drill presses, angle grinders, belt sanders, and wax trimmers.</p>

