      <h2>Maintenance and Lubrication</h2>

      <h3>Handpiece</h3>
      <p>No lubrication is required for the handpiece. The ball bearings are pre-lubricated and shielded.</p>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Do not put oil or grease into the front or back of the handpiece.</strong> Doing so will damage the pre-lubricated ball bearings.
      </div>

      <p>Keep the collet seat and chuck free of dirt, chips, dust, and debris.</p>

      <h3>Flexible Shaft</h3>

      <div class="note">
        Clean and lubricate the flexible shaft every 50 hours of use.
      </div>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h30/p00_05.jpg" alt="Removing the inner shaft from the sheath for cleaning and lubrication" />
        <figcaption>Remove the inner shaft from the sheath for cleaning and re-greasing</figcaption>
      </div>

      <ol>
        <li>Unplug your power tool.</li>
        <li>Remove the handpiece from the shaft.</li>
        <li>Loosen the set screw in the motor connector and remove the sheath.</li>
        <li>Wipe the exposed shaft clean with a cloth and solvent.</li>
        <li>Apply a light film of Foredom grease (part no. MS10006) to the entire length of the inner shaft.</li>
        <li>Reconnect the shaft and sheath, following the adjustment procedure above.</li>
        <li>Run the motor for ten minutes before reconnecting the handpiece to redistribute the grease.</li>
        <li>Turn off the motor, wipe off excess grease from the tip of the drive shaft, and reconnect the handpiece.</li>
      </ol>

